The paper discusses the problem of vocabulary mismatch in information retrieval, which is a core topic in the field of information retrieval (cs.IR). The paper also focuses on the use of neural models for semantic matching, which is a subfield of natural language processing (cs.CL) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper discusses the use of these models for tasks such as query suggestion, ad retrieval, and document retrieval, which are all common tasks in web search (cs.AI). Finally, the paper mentions the use of resources and best practices, which could potentially involve the use of computer vision techniques for image retrieval (cs.CV).
